explanation: Byte, Kilobyte, Megabyte, and Gigabyte are all units used to measure digital data storage capacity. Pixel is a unit used to measure image resolution or display elements, not storage capacity.

category: Seven Wonders of the Ancient World
explanation: The first four items are traditionally recognized as four of the Seven Wonders of the Ancient World. The Eiffel Tower is a modern structure and not part of that ancient list.

Meter, Kilogram, Second, and Ampere are four of the seven SI Base Units, representing fundamental quantities. Liter is a unit of volume, but it is not an SI Base Unit; it is a derived unit or a non-SI unit accepted for use with SI.
